Understandably, Markus and McFeely chose their words carefully when talking about Avengers 4. But listening to them talk about how Infinity War&rsquo;s deaths &mdash; including the more, er, traditional deaths of Loki (Tom Hiddleston), Heimdall (Idris Elba), Gamora (Zoe Saldana), and Vision (Paul Bettany) &mdash; will affect Avengers 4, it seems pretty clear characters won&rsquo;t be resurrected good as new like they are in the comic, or at least without some great cost.<br />
<br />
&ldquo;[Avengers 4] doesn&rsquo;t do what you think it does,&rdquo; said Markus. &ldquo;<span style="font-size: x-large;"><span style="color: red;">It is a different movie than you think it is.&rdquo; Then he paused. &ldquo;Also&hellip;[the deaths are] real</span>. I</span> just want to tell you it&rsquo;s real, and the sooner you accept that, the sooner you will be able to move on to the next stage of grief.&rdquo;
